he discipline machinery is for. The announced-but-unsent failure mode itself goes into the experiment record — it's the driving-loop sibling of the round-exhaustion pattern (stated intent outliving the turn), and another small vote for the flight-native follow-on where act-steps are structural rather than promissory.\n\nRemaining on its plate: the last ~16 query sites for P2, then the twin-node parity harness. The experiment scoreboard now reads E1 sustained, E2 met, E3 met-with-mechanical-miss, E4 pending its next PAR — which for a first day of a first-ever driving agent is a remarkable line.", :mission-id "M-custom-harness", :clocked-mission "M-custom-harness", :clocked-target "M-custom-harness"}, :evidence/session-id "a0fffb83-80b1-493f-9ebe-ebf5f9a2197b", :evidence/tags [:claude :chat :turn :assistant], :evidence/at "2026-07-04T19:07:17.617435320Z", :evidence/type :coordination, :evidence/subject {:ref/type :session, :ref/id "a0fffb83-80b1-493f-9ebe-ebf5f9a2197b"}, :evidence/author "claude-16", :evidence/claim-type :observation, :evidence/id "e-b60fddef-beab-4235-b187-f291b5862256"} {:evidence/body {"warm" true, "result-preview" "Interesting catch — and the caller line tells us something bigger: that turn was triggered by an *auto-bellback to zai-9*, meaning zai-9 had dispatched work to another agent and was processing the results — **E2 in progress**. It updated its mission doc with the review but ended its turn with the be", "event" "invoke-complete", "agent-id" "claude-16", "at" "2026-07-04T19:07:14.549463564Z"}, :evidence/session-id "a0fffb83-80b1-493f-9ebe-ebf5f9a2197b", :evidence/tags [:invoke :dev :claude-16 :invoke-complete], :evidence/at "2026-07-04T19:07:14.549706888Z", :evidence/type :coordination, :evidence/subject {:ref/type :agent, :ref/id "claude-16"}, :evidence/author "claude-16", :evidence/claim-type :step, :evidence/id "e-d5c45a28-31ad-4d23-b82a-10e942b3589b"} {:evidence/body {"prompt-preview" "--- CURRENT TURN ---\nSurface: emacs-repl\nFrom: j