on, tool results are truncated to 12k chars each but never dropped. For bell-executors this never mattered (short sessions, then discarded). But **zai-9 is designed to drive a mission across many turns on one session** — mission-length accumulation will degrade quality and cost, then hit the context ceiling. The mitigation is cheap and we already own the machinery: a rolling window (system message + last N turns) with trimmed turns folded into a rehydration-style summary block — the exact pattern D-7 built, applied *inside* a live session instead of across sessions.\n\nSo my recommendation: skip pouches entirely; do transcript persistence when convenient; and treat compaction as the real successor item — with zai-9's own mission as the empirical trigger. Its session is the first that will grow long enough to measure, so we watch its context length as it drives, and build the rolling window when the curve says so rather than speculatively. Fittingly, the driving experiment stress-tests the harness in exactly the dimension the harness hasn't been tested. I'll note both items in the M-custom-harness doc as named follow-ons — they're DOCUMENT-phase material now.", :mission-id "M-custom-harness", :clocked-mission "M-custom-harness", :clocked-target "M-custom-harness"}, :evidence/session-id "a0fffb83-80b1-493f-9ebe-ebf5f9a2197b", :evidence/tags [:claude :chat :turn :assistant], :evidence/at "2026-07-04T18:59:00.250604948Z", :evidence/type :coordination, :evidence/subject {:ref/type :session, :ref/id "a0fffb83-80b1-493f-9ebe-ebf5f9a2197b"}, :evidence/author "claude-16", :evidence/claim-type :observation, :evidence/id "e-08332862-a2c0-4f91-b12b-e775b6a4db37"} {:evidence/body {"warm" true, "result-preview" "Good question to ask now, because the answer splits cleanly along an architecture line. Quick ground-truth check on the one claim I want to make about context growth:Short answer: **pouches, no — but the question uncovers the upgrade zai-9 actually will need, and it's a d