en a limit-2000 query times out → the store needs compaction/pruning).\n\nThe design smell you named is the actual root — and it's a nice one, because it's *self-worsening* (each completion grows the store that slows the next completion-check), which explains why this kept recurring. Two clean follow-ups when you want them, both scoped work rather than live patches:\n1. **Replace scan-for-completion with a maintained done-set** (the dispatcher already knows what it kicked — record completions locally).\n2. **Store compaction/pruning** of old ephemeral evidence (the `store.clj` compact path + the gated erase path we built earlier this session are the machinery).\n\nThat's a good place to rest it. Nothing's on fire, the mesh is working, and the principle's written down so it doesn't get re-discovered the hard way next time."}, :evidence/session-id "23b70755-aaf1-4cc7-8a4a-39db7645bcba", :evidence/tags [:claude :chat :turn :assistant], :evidence/at "2026-07-04T18:20:01.279492828Z", :evidence/type :coordination, :evidence/subject {:ref/type :session, :ref/id "23b70755-aaf1-4cc7-8a4a-39db7645bcba"}, :evidence/author "claude-10", :evidence/claim-type :observation, :evidence/id "e-b5c5af3b-51ed-4bd6-8e6c-df39d39d04ca"} {:evidence/body {"warm" true, "result-preview" "Strong agree — and you've named the actual root, which is a *design* smell, not just a perf one:\n\n**Scanning the whole evidence store to reconstruct \"what's already done\" is backwards.** `completed-entity-ids` / `completed-problem-ids` were doing exactly that — reading the entire corpus every time t", "event" "invoke-complete", "agent-id" "claude-10", "at" "2026-07-04T18:19:57.625353433Z"}, :evidence/session-id "23b70755-aaf1-4cc7-8a4a-39db7645bcba", :evidence/tags [:invoke :dev :claude-10 :invoke-complete], :evidence/at "2026-07-04T18:19:57.626137277Z", :evidence/type :coordination, :evidence/subject {:ref/type :agent, :ref/id "claude-10"}, :evidence/author "claude-10", :evidence/claim-type :step, :evidenc